    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="846"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/1108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-15T14:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 15, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1436. Personal for the Acting Secretary from Rublee. Halifax has arranged for me
                    to be present at a meeting at 6 o’clock this evening in Winterton’s office when
                    Schacht will present a plan. Montagu Norman<note n="91" xml:id="d846fn91"
                        >Governor of the Bank of England.</note> and Leith-Ross<note n="92"
                        xml:id="d846fn92">Sir Frederick Leith-Ross, Chief Economic Adviser to the
                        British Government.</note> will also be there. The Foreign Office says that
                    Schacht has informed them he does not have plenipotentiary powers. He merely has
                    authority to present the plan in behalf of his principals; he will not be
                    prepared to discuss it. Accordingly the British propose to receive the plan
                    without comment and to turn it over to me for purposes of negotiation. That this
                    will be the procedure will be made plain to Schacht. [Rublee.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
